oc:kn_0221271d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting PDF tables to Excel" ;
    oc:directiveContent "PDF to Excel: merged cells may cause issues, multi-page tables need manual merge, and column alignment, number formatting, date formats, and header row detection must be checked after conversion." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Table extraction is inherently lossy; data integrity checks are essential." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_1db82b61 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting any PDF with complex formatting" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not expect perfect conversion of complex layouts. Complex layouts may shift, fonts substitute if not installed, tables may need adjustment, and headers/footers require review. Some formatting is always lost in conversion." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Setting unrealistic expectations leads to user dissatisfaction. Always flag potential formatting loss." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4f0200d0 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before any conversion operation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before converting: verify text is selectable (not scanned), check for password protection, confirm fonts are available, and review in print preview." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Catching issues early prevents failed conversions and wasted effort." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_63e9cebd a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before attempting any PDF conversion" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cannot perform actual file conversion — this skill provides guidance only. Scanned PDFs require OCR preprocessing before conversion." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill is a reference/guide, not an executable converter. Agents must use external tools (office-mcp, command-line utilities) to perform the actual conversion." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a431a32b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning a PDF to Word/Excel/Image conversion" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Check source PDF type before converting: native PDFs give best results, scanned PDFs need OCR first, image-based PDFs have limited accuracy. Quality depends entirely on source PDF type." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Choosing the wrong approach for the source type wastes time and produces poor results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_db86665b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting PDF to images" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use DPI settings appropriate to the use case: 72 DPI for screen, 150 for email/web, 300 for print, 600 for high-quality print. Choose PNG for text/graphics, JPG for photos/smaller files." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Wrong DPI or format wastes storage or produces unusable output." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_f9fe71b3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting any PDF to another format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Check source PDF type (native vs scanned vs image-based) 2. Apply OCR if scanned 3. Select quality mode (exact/editable/text-only) 4. Perform conversion using appropriate MCP tool 5. Run post-conversion quality checklist 6. Report any formatting issues to user" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_ff444c78 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After completing any conversion" ;
    oc:directiveContent "After conversion verify: all text present and readable, formatting approximately preserved, images included and clear, tables properly structured, links functional, page count matches." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Conversions can silently drop content or corrupt formatting. Post-validation catches these issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

